{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"Good morning everyone. First of all, it's been fantastic"},{"time":5000,"text":"being here over these past few days."},{"time":8000,"text":"And secondly, I feel it's a great honor to kind of wind up"},{"time":12000,"text":"this extraordinary gathering of people,"},{"time":14000,"text":"these amazing talks that we've had."},{"time":17000,"text":"I feel that I've fitted in, in many ways,"},{"time":20000,"text":"to some of the things that I've heard."},{"time":23000,"text":"I came directly here"},{"time":27000,"text":"from the deep, deep tropical rainforest in Ecuador,"},{"time":32000,"text":"where I was out -- you could only get there by a plane --"},{"time":35000,"text":"with indigenous people with paint on their faces"},{"time":39000,"text":"and parrot feathers on their headdresses,"},{"time":41000,"text":"where these people are fighting to try and keep the oil companies,"},{"time":46000,"text":"and keep the roads, out of their forests."},{"time":50000,"text":"They're fighting to develop their own way of living within the forest"},{"time":54000,"text":"in a world that's clean, a world that isn't contaminated,"},{"time":57000,"text":"a world that isn't polluted."},{"time":60000,"text":"And what was so amazing to me, and what fits right in"},{"time":63000,"text":"with what we're all talking about here at TED,"},{"time":66000,"text":"is that there, right in the middle of this rainforest,"},{"time":69000,"text":"was some solar panels -- the first in that part of Ecuador --"},{"time":74000,"text":"and that was mainly to bring water up by pump"},{"time":77000,"text":"so that the women wouldn't have to go down."},{"time":79000,"text":"The water was cleaned, but because they got a lot of batteries,"},{"time":82000,"text":"they were able to store a lot of electricity."},{"time":85000,"text":"So every house -- and there were, I think, eight houses"},{"time":87000,"text":"in this little community -- could have light"},{"time":90000,"text":"for, I think it was about half an hour each evening."},{"time":93000,"text":"And there is the Chief, in all his regal finery, with a laptop computer."},{"time":99000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":101000,"text":"And this man, he has been outside, but he's gone back,"},{"time":106000,"text":"and he was saying, \"You know, we have suddenly jumped into"},{"time":112000,"text":"a whole new era, and we didn't even know about the white man"},{"time":116000,"text":"50 years ago, and now here we are with laptop computers,"},{"time":119000,"text":"and there are some things we want to learn from the modern world."},{"time":122000,"text":"We want to know about health care."},{"time":125000,"text":"We want to know about what other people do -- we're interested in it."},{"time":129000,"text":"And we want to learn other languages."},{"time":131000,"text":"We want to know English and French and perhaps Chinese,"},{"time":135000,"text":"and we're good at languages.\""},{"time":137000,"text":"So there he is with his little laptop computer,"},{"time":141000,"text":"but fighting against the might of the pressures --"},{"time":145000,"text":"because of the debt, the foreign debt of Ecuador --"},{"time":148000,"text":"fighting the pressure of World Bank, IMF, and of course"},{"time":152000,"text":"the people who want to exploit the forests and take out the oil."},{"time":157000,"text":"And so, coming directly from there to here."},{"time":161000,"text":"But, of course, my real field of expertise"},{"time":164000,"text":"lies in an even different kind of civilization --"},{"time":168000,"text":"I can't really call it a civilization."},{"time":171000,"text":"A different way of life, a different being."},{"time":175000,"text":"We've talked earlier -- this wonderful talk by Wade Davis"},{"time":180000,"text":"about the different cultures of the humans around the world --"},{"time":183000,"text":"but the world is not composed only of human beings;"},{"time":188000,"text":"there are also other animal beings."},{"time":190000,"text":"And I propose to bring into this TED conference,"},{"time":193000,"text":"as I always do around the world, the voice of the animal kingdom."},{"time":197000,"text":"Too often we just see a few slides, or a bit of film,"},{"time":200000,"text":"but these beings have voices that mean something."},{"time":203000,"text":"And so, I want to give you a greeting,"},{"time":205000,"text":"as from a chimpanzee in the forests of Tanzania --"},{"time":209000,"text":"Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh!"},{"time":216000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":225000,"text":"I've been studying chimpanzees in Tanzania since 1960."},{"time":230000,"text":"During that time, there have been modern technologies"},{"time":234000,"text":"that have really transformed the way"},{"time":236000,"text":"that field biologists do their work."},{"time":239000,"text":"For example, for the first time, a few years ago,"},{"time":242000,"text":"by simply collecting little fecal samples"},{"time":245000,"text":"we were able to have them analyzed -- to have DNA profiling done --"},{"time":250000,"text":"so for the first time, we actually know which male chimps"},{"time":254000,"text":"are the fathers of each individual infant."},{"time":257000,"text":"Because the chimps have a very promiscuous mating society."},{"time":261000,"text":"So this opens up a whole new avenue of research."},{"time":264000,"text":"And we use GSI -- geographic whatever it is, GSI --"},{"time":271000,"text":"to determine the range of the chimps."},{"time":275000,"text":"And we're using -- you can see that I'm not really into this kind of stuff --"},{"time":281000,"text":"but we're using satellite imagery"},{"time":284000,"text":"to look at the deforestation in the area."},{"time":287000,"text":"And of course, there's developments in infrared,"},{"time":290000,"text":"so you can watch animals at night,"},{"time":292000,"text":"and equipment for recording by video,"},{"time":295000,"text":"and tape recording is getting lighter and better."},{"time":298000,"text":"So in many, many ways, we can do things today"},{"time":301000,"text":"that we couldn't do when I began in 1960."},{"time":306000,"text":"Especially when chimpanzees, and other animals"},{"time":309000,"text":"with large brains, are studied in captivity,"},{"time":311000,"text":"modern technology is helping us to search"},{"time":316000,"text":"for the upper levels of cognition in some of these non-human animals."},{"time":320000,"text":"So that we know today, they're capable of performances"},{"time":324000,"text":"that would have been thought absolutely impossible"},{"time":326000,"text":"by science when I began."},{"time":329000,"text":"I think the chimpanzee in captivity who is the most skilled"},{"time":333000,"text":"in intellectual performance is one called Ai in Japan --"},{"time":337000,"text":"her name means love --"},{"time":339000,"text":"and she has a wonderfully sensitive partner working with her."},{"time":343000,"text":"She loves her computer --"},{"time":345000,"text":"she'll leave her big group, and her running water,"},{"time":348000,"text":"and her trees and everything."},{"time":350000,"text":"And she'll come in to sit at this computer --"},{"time":352000,"text":"it's like a video game for a kid; she's hooked."},{"time":354000,"text":"She's 28, by the way, and she does things with her computer screen"},{"time":358000,"text":"and a touch pad that she can do faster than most humans."},{"time":364000,"text":"She does very complex tasks, and I haven't got time to go into them,"},{"time":369000,"text":"but the amazing thing about this female is"},{"time":371000,"text":"she doesn't like making mistakes."},{"time":375000,"text":"If she has a bad run, and her score isn't good,"},{"time":378000,"text":"she'll come and reach up and tap on the glass --"},{"time":380000,"text":"because she can't see the experimenter --"},{"time":382000,"text":"which is asking to have another go."},{"time":385000,"text":"And her concentration -- she's already concentrated hard"},{"time":388000,"text":"for 20 minutes or so, and now she wants to do it all over again,"},{"time":392000,"text":"just for the satisfaction of having done it better."},{"time":395000,"text":"And the food is not important -- she does get a tiny reward,"},{"time":398000,"text":"like one raisin for a correct response --"},{"time":401000,"text":"but she will do it for nothing, if you tell her beforehand."},{"time":405000,"text":"So here we are, a chimpanzee using a computer."},{"time":410000,"text":"Chimpanzees, gorillas, orangutans also learn human sign language."},{"time":414000,"text":"But the point is that when I was first in Gombe in 1960 --"},{"time":419000,"text":"I remember so well, so vividly, as though it was yesterday --"},{"time":423000,"text":"the first time, when I was going through the vegetation,"},{"time":426000,"text":"the chimpanzees were still running away from me, for the most part,"},{"time":429000,"text":"although some were a little bit acclimatized --"},{"time":433000,"text":"and I saw this dark shape, hunched over a termite mound,"},{"time":437000,"text":"and I peered with my binoculars."},{"time":439000,"text":"It was, fortunately, one adult male whom I'd named David Greybeard --"},{"time":444000,"text":"and by the way, science at that time was telling me that I shouldn't name the chimps;"},{"time":447000,"text":"they should all have numbers; that was more scientific."},{"time":449000,"text":"Anyway, David Greybeard -- and I saw that"},{"time":452000,"text":"he was picking little pieces of grass and using them"},{"time":456000,"text":"to fish termites from their underground nest."},{"time":459000,"text":"And not only that -- he would sometimes pick a leafy twig"},{"time":462000,"text":"and strip the leaves --"},{"time":464000,"text":"modifying an object to make it suitable for a specific purpose --"},{"time":467000,"text":"the beginning of tool-making."},{"time":470000,"text":"The reason this was so exciting and such a breakthrough"},{"time":472000,"text":"is at that time, it was thought that humans,"},{"time":475000,"text":"and only humans, used and made tools."},{"time":478000,"text":"When I was at school, we were defined as man, the toolmaker."},{"time":482000,"text":"So that when Louis Leakey, my mentor, heard this news,"},{"time":486000,"text":"he said, \"Ah, we must now redefine 'man,' redefine 'tool,'"},{"time":489000,"text":"or accept chimpanzees as humans.\""},{"time":492000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":494000,"text":"We now know that at Gombe alone, there are nine different ways"},{"time":498000,"text":"in which chimpanzees use different objects for different purposes."},{"time":502000,"text":"Moreover, we know that in different parts of Africa,"},{"time":504000,"text":"wherever chimps have been studied,"},{"time":506000,"text":"there are completely different tool-using behaviors."},{"time":511000,"text":"And because it seems that these patterns are passed"},{"time":514000,"text":"from one generation to the next, through observation,"},{"time":517000,"text":"imitation and practice -- that is a definition of human culture."},{"time":522000,"text":"What we find is that over these 40-odd years"},{"time":526000,"text":"that I and others have been studying chimpanzees"},{"time":529000,"text":"and the other great apes, and, as I say, other mammals"},{"time":532000,"text":"with complex brains and social systems,"},{"time":535000,"text":"we have found that after all, there isn't a sharp line"},{"time":539000,"text":"dividing humans from the rest of the animal kingdom."},{"time":542000,"text":"It's a very wuzzy line."},{"time":544000,"text":"It's getting wuzzier all the time as we find animals doing things"},{"time":547000,"text":"that we, in our arrogance, used to think was just human."},{"time":552000,"text":"The chimps -- there's no time to discuss their fascinating lives --"},{"time":556000,"text":"but they have this long childhood, five years"},{"time":559000,"text":"of suckling and sleeping with the mother,"},{"time":561000,"text":"and then another three, four or five years"},{"time":563000,"text":"of emotional dependence on her, even when the next child is born."},{"time":568000,"text":"The importance of learning in that time, when behavior is flexible --"},{"time":571000,"text":"and there's an awful lot to learn in chimpanzee society."},{"time":575000,"text":"The long-term affectionate supportive bonds"},{"time":578000,"text":"that develop throughout this long childhood with the mother,"},{"time":581000,"text":"with the brothers and sisters,"},{"time":583000,"text":"and which can last through a lifetime,"},{"time":586000,"text":"which may be up to 60 years."},{"time":588000,"text":"They can actually live longer than 60 in captivity,"},{"time":591000,"text":"so we've only done 40 years in the wild so far."},{"time":594000,"text":"And we find chimps are capable of true compassion and altruism."},{"time":600000,"text":"We find in their non-verbal communication -- this is very rich --"},{"time":604000,"text":"they have a lot of sounds, which they use in different circumstances,"},{"time":609000,"text":"but they also use touch, posture, gesture,"},{"time":611000,"text":"and what do they do?"},{"time":613000,"text":"They kiss; they embrace; they hold hands."},{"time":615000,"text":"They pat one another on the back; they swagger; they shake their fist --"},{"time":618000,"text":"the kind of things that we do,"},{"time":621000,"text":"and they do them in the same kind of context."},{"time":624000,"text":"They have very sophisticated cooperation."},{"time":626000,"text":"Sometimes they hunt -- not that often,"},{"time":629000,"text":"but when they hunt, they show sophisticated cooperation,"},{"time":632000,"text":"and they share the prey."},{"time":635000,"text":"We find that they show emotions, similar to -- maybe sometimes the same --"},{"time":641000,"text":"as those that we describe in ourselves as happiness, sadness, fear, despair."},{"time":646000,"text":"They know mental as well as physical suffering."},{"time":648000,"text":"And I don't have time to go into the information"},{"time":651000,"text":"that will prove some of these things to you,"},{"time":653000,"text":"save to say that there are very bright students, in the best universities,"},{"time":657000,"text":"studying emotions in animals, studying personalities in animals."},{"time":661000,"text":"We know that chimpanzees and some other creatures"},{"time":664000,"text":"can recognize themselves in mirrors -- \"self\" as opposed to \"other.\""},{"time":669000,"text":"They have a sense of humor, and these are the kind of things"},{"time":673000,"text":"which traditionally have been thought of as human prerogatives."},{"time":679000,"text":"But this teaches us a new respect -- and it's a new respect"},{"time":684000,"text":"not only for the chimpanzees, I suggest,"},{"time":687000,"text":"but some of the other amazing animals with whom we share this planet."},{"time":691000,"text":"Once we're prepared to admit that after all,"},{"time":694000,"text":"we're not the only beings with personalities, minds"},{"time":697000,"text":"and above all feelings, and then we start to think"},{"time":699000,"text":"about ways we use and abuse"},{"time":701000,"text":"so many other sentient, sapient creatures on this planet,"},{"time":707000,"text":"it really gives cause for deep shame, at least for me."},{"time":714000,"text":"So, the sad thing is that these chimpanzees --"},{"time":718000,"text":"who've perhaps taught us, more than any other creature, a little humility --"},{"time":722000,"text":"are in the wild, disappearing very fast."},{"time":725000,"text":"They're disappearing for the reasons"},{"time":727000,"text":"that all of you in this room know only too well."},{"time":730000,"text":"The deforestation, the growth of human populations, needing more land."},{"time":735000,"text":"They're disappearing because some timber companies"},{"time":738000,"text":"go in with clear-cutting."},{"time":740000,"text":"They're disappearing in the heart of their range in Africa"},{"time":744000,"text":"because the big multinational logging companies have come in and made roads --"},{"time":749000,"text":"as they want to do in Ecuador"},{"time":751000,"text":"and other parts where the forests remain untouched --"},{"time":754000,"text":"to take out oil or timber."},{"time":758000,"text":"And this has led in Congo basin, and other parts of the world,"},{"time":763000,"text":"to what is known as the bush-meat trade."},{"time":765000,"text":"This means that although for hundreds, perhaps thousands of years,"},{"time":769000,"text":"people have lived in those forests, or whatever habitat it is,"},{"time":773000,"text":"in harmony with their world, just killing the animals they need"},{"time":776000,"text":"for themselves and their families --"},{"time":778000,"text":"now, suddenly, because of the roads,"},{"time":781000,"text":"the hunters can go in from the towns."},{"time":783000,"text":"They shoot everything, every single thing that moves"},{"time":786000,"text":"that's bigger than a small rat; they sun-dry it or smoke it."},{"time":791000,"text":"And now they've got transport; they take it on the logging trucks"},{"time":794000,"text":"or the mining trucks into the towns where they sell it."},{"time":798000,"text":"And people will pay more for bush-meat, as it's called,"},{"time":803000,"text":"than for domestic meat -- it's culturally preferred."},{"time":806000,"text":"And it's not sustainable, and the huge logging camps in the forest"},{"time":810000,"text":"are now demanding meat, so the Pygmy hunters in the Congo basin"},{"time":814000,"text":"who've lived there with their wonderful way of living"},{"time":818000,"text":"for so many hundreds of years are now corrupted."},{"time":821000,"text":"They're given weapons; they shoot for the logging camps; they get money."},{"time":824000,"text":"Their culture is being destroyed,"},{"time":827000,"text":"along with the animals upon whom they depend."},{"time":830000,"text":"So, when the logging camp moves, there's nothing left."},{"time":833000,"text":"We talked already about the loss of human cultural diversity,"},{"time":836000,"text":"and I've seen it happening with my own eyes."},{"time":839000,"text":"And the grim picture in Africa -- I love Africa,"},{"time":843000,"text":"and what do we see in Africa?"},{"time":845000,"text":"We see deforestation;"},{"time":848000,"text":"we see the desert spreading; we see massive hunger;"},{"time":853000,"text":"we see disease and we see population growth in areas"},{"time":857000,"text":"where there are more people living on a certain piece of land"},{"time":861000,"text":"than the land can possibly support,"},{"time":863000,"text":"and they're too poor to buy food from elsewhere."},{"time":866000,"text":"Were the people that we heard about yesterday,"},{"time":869000,"text":"on the Easter Island, who cut down their last tree -- were they stupid?"},{"time":873000,"text":"Didn't they know what was happening?"},{"time":875000,"text":"Of course, but if you've seen the crippling poverty"},{"time":877000,"text":"in some of these parts of the world"},{"time":879000,"text":"it isn't a question of \"Let's leave the tree for tomorrow.\""},{"time":882000,"text":"\"How am I going to feed my family today?"},{"time":884000,"text":"Maybe I can get just a few dollars from this last tree"},{"time":887000,"text":"which will keep us going a little bit longer,"},{"time":889000,"text":"and then we'll pray that something will happen"},{"time":892000,"text":"to save us from the inevitable end.\""},{"time":895000,"text":"So, this is a pretty grim picture."},{"time":898000,"text":"The one thing we have, which makes us so different"},{"time":902000,"text":"from chimpanzees or other living creatures,"},{"time":904000,"text":"is this sophisticated spoken language --"},{"time":907000,"text":"a language with which we can tell children"},{"time":909000,"text":"about things that aren't here."},{"time":911000,"text":"We can talk about the distant past, plan for the distant future,"},{"time":915000,"text":"discuss ideas with each other,"},{"time":917000,"text":"so that the ideas can grow from the accumulated wisdom of a group."},{"time":921000,"text":"We can do it by talking to each other;"},{"time":923000,"text":"we can do it through video; we can do it through the written word."},{"time":927000,"text":"And we are abusing this great power we have to be wise stewards,"},{"time":932000,"text":"and we're destroying the world."},{"time":934000,"text":"In the developed world, in a way, it's worse,"},{"time":937000,"text":"because we have so much access to knowledge"},{"time":940000,"text":"of the stupidity of what we're doing."},{"time":942000,"text":"Do you know, we're bringing little babies"},{"time":945000,"text":"into a world where, in many places, the water is poisoning them?"},{"time":950000,"text":"And the air is harming them, and the food that's grown"},{"time":954000,"text":"from the contaminated land is poisoning them."},{"time":957000,"text":"And that's not just in the far-away developing world; that's everywhere."},{"time":961000,"text":"Do you know we all have about 50 chemicals"},{"time":963000,"text":"in our bodies we didn't have about 50 years ago?"},{"time":967000,"text":"And so many of these diseases, like asthma"},{"time":971000,"text":"and certain kinds of cancers, are on the increase"},{"time":974000,"text":"around places where our filthy toxic waste is dumped."},{"time":979000,"text":"We're harming ourselves around the world,"},{"time":982000,"text":"as well as harming the animals, as well as harming nature herself --"},{"time":986000,"text":"Mother Nature, that brought us into being;"},{"time":989000,"text":"Mother Nature, where I believe we need to spend time,"},{"time":993000,"text":"where there's trees and flowers and birds"},{"time":995000,"text":"for our good psychological development."},{"time":998000,"text":"And yet, there are hundreds and hundreds of children"},{"time":1001000,"text":"in the developed world who never see nature,"},{"time":1003000,"text":"because they're growing up in concrete"},{"time":1005000,"text":"and all they know is virtual reality,"},{"time":1007000,"text":"with no opportunity to go and lie in the sun,"},{"time":1011000,"text":"or in the forest, with the dappled sun-specks"},{"time":1014000,"text":"coming down from the canopy above."},{"time":1017000,"text":"As I was traveling around the world, you know,"},{"time":1020000,"text":"I had to leave the forest -- that's where I love to be."},{"time":1023000,"text":"I had to leave these fascinating chimpanzees"},{"time":1026000,"text":"for my students and field staff to continue studying"},{"time":1030000,"text":"because, finding they dwindled from about two million"},{"time":1033000,"text":"100 years ago to about 150,000 now,"},{"time":1037000,"text":"I knew I had to leave the forest to do what I could"},{"time":1040000,"text":"to raise awareness around the world."},{"time":1042000,"text":"And the more I talked about the chimpanzees' plight,"},{"time":1045000,"text":"the more I realized the fact that everything's interconnected,"},{"time":1050000,"text":"and the problems of the developing world"},{"time":1052000,"text":"so often stem from the greed of the developed world,"},{"time":1055000,"text":"and everything was joining together, and making -- not sense,"},{"time":1060000,"text":"hope lies in sense, you said -- it's making a nonsense."},{"time":1064000,"text":"How can we do it?"},{"time":1065000,"text":"Somebody said that yesterday."},{"time":1067000,"text":"And as I was traveling around, I kept meeting young people who'd lost hope."},{"time":1072000,"text":"They were feeling despair,"},{"time":1075000,"text":"they were feeling, \"Well, it doesn't matter what we do;"},{"time":1078000,"text":"eat, drink and be merry, for tomorrow we die."},{"time":1080000,"text":"Everything is hopeless -- we're always being told so by the media.\""},{"time":1084000,"text":"And then I met some who were angry,"},{"time":1087000,"text":"and anger that can turn to violence,"},{"time":1089000,"text":"and we're all familiar with that."},{"time":1092000,"text":"And I have three little grandchildren,"},{"time":1096000,"text":"and when some of these students would say to me"},{"time":1099000,"text":"at high school or university, they'd say, \"We're angry,\""},{"time":1102000,"text":"or \"We're filled with despair, because we feel"},{"time":1105000,"text":"you've compromised our future, and there's nothing we can do about it.\""},{"time":1109000,"text":"And I looked in the eyes of my little grandchildren,"},{"time":1111000,"text":"and think how much we've harmed this planet since I was their age."},{"time":1115000,"text":"I feel this deep shame, and that's why in 1991 in Tanzania,"},{"time":1121000,"text":"I started a program that's called Roots and Shoots."},{"time":1124000,"text":"There's little brochures all around outside,"},{"time":1128000,"text":"and if any of you have anything to do with children and care about their future,"},{"time":1132000,"text":"I beg that you pick up that brochure."},{"time":1135000,"text":"And Roots and Shoots is a program for hope."},{"time":1139000,"text":"Roots make a firm foundation."},{"time":1141000,"text":"Shoots seem tiny,"},{"time":1143000,"text":"but to reach the sun they can break through brick walls."},{"time":1146000,"text":"See the brick walls as all the problems"},{"time":1148000,"text":"that we've inflicted on this planet."},{"time":1150000,"text":"Then, you see, it is a message of hope."},{"time":1154000,"text":"Hundreds and thousands of young people around the world"},{"time":1156000,"text":"can break through, and can make this a better world."},{"time":1160000,"text":"And the most important message of Roots and Shoots"},{"time":1163000,"text":"is that every single individual makes a difference."},{"time":1167000,"text":"Every individual has a role to play."},{"time":1169000,"text":"Every one of us impacts the world around us everyday,"},{"time":1173000,"text":"and you scientists know that you can't actually --"},{"time":1176000,"text":"even if you stay in bed all day, you're breathing oxygen"},{"time":1179000,"text":"and giving out CO2, and probably going to the loo,"},{"time":1183000,"text":"and things like that --"},{"time":1185000,"text":"you're making a difference in the world."},{"time":1187000,"text":"So, the Roots and Shoots program"},{"time":1190000,"text":"involves youth in three kinds of projects."},{"time":1195000,"text":"And these are projects to make the world around them a better place."},{"time":1199000,"text":"One project to show care and concern for your own human community."},{"time":1205000,"text":"One for animals, including domestic animals -- and I have to say,"},{"time":1209000,"text":"I learned everything I know about animal behavior"},{"time":1211000,"text":"even before I got to Gombe and the chimps from my dog, Rusty,"},{"time":1215000,"text":"who was my childhood companion."},{"time":1218000,"text":"And the third kind of project: something for the local environment."},{"time":1223000,"text":"So what the kids do depends first of all, how old are they --"},{"time":1227000,"text":"and we go now from pre-school right through university."},{"time":1231000,"text":"It's going to depend whether they're inner-city or rural."},{"time":1234000,"text":"It's going to depend if they're wealthy or impoverished."},{"time":1239000,"text":"It's going to depend which part, say, of America they're in."},{"time":1242000,"text":"We're in every state now, and the problems in Florida"},{"time":1245000,"text":"are different from the problems in New York."},{"time":1248000,"text":"It's going to depend on which country they're in --"},{"time":1250000,"text":"and we're already in 60-plus countries, with about 5,000 active groups --"},{"time":1256000,"text":"and there are groups all over the place that I keep hearing about"},{"time":1260000,"text":"that I've never even heard of, because the kids are taking the program"},{"time":1263000,"text":"and spreading it themselves."},{"time":1265000,"text":"Why?"},{"time":1267000,"text":"Because they're buying into it,"},{"time":1269000,"text":"and they're the ones who get to decide what they're going to do."},{"time":1272000,"text":"It isn't something that their parents tell them,"},{"time":1274000,"text":"or their teachers tell them."},{"time":1276000,"text":"That's effective, but if they decide themselves,"},{"time":1279000,"text":"\"We want to clean this river"},{"time":1282000,"text":"and put the fish back that used to be there."},{"time":1284000,"text":"We want to clear away the toxic soil"},{"time":1289000,"text":"from this area and have an organic garden."},{"time":1291000,"text":"We want to go and spend time with the old people"},{"time":1294000,"text":"and hear their stories and record their oral histories."},{"time":1299000,"text":"We want to go and work in a dog shelter."},{"time":1301000,"text":"We want to learn about animals. We want ... \""},{"time":1303000,"text":"You know, it goes on and on, and this is very hopeful for me."},{"time":1307000,"text":"As I travel around the world 300 days a year,"},{"time":1311000,"text":"everywhere there's a group of Roots and Shoots of different ages."},{"time":1314000,"text":"Everywhere there are children with shining eyes saying,"},{"time":1316000,"text":"\"Look at the difference we've made.\""},{"time":1319000,"text":"And now comes the technology into it,"},{"time":1321000,"text":"because with this new way of communicating electronically"},{"time":1326000,"text":"these kids can communicate with each other around the world."},{"time":1330000,"text":"And if anyone is interested to help us, we've got so many ideas"},{"time":1333000,"text":"but we need help -- we need help to create the right kind of system"},{"time":1339000,"text":"that will help these young people to communicate their excitement."},{"time":1343000,"text":"But also -- and this is so important -- to communicate their despair,"},{"time":1348000,"text":"to say, \"We've tried this and it doesn't work, and what shall we do?\""},{"time":1351000,"text":"And then, lo and behold, there's another group answering these kids"},{"time":1355000,"text":"who may be in America, or maybe this is a group in Israel,"},{"time":1358000,"text":"saying, \"Yeah, you did it a little bit wrong. This is how you should do it.\""},{"time":1363000,"text":"The philosophy is very simple."},{"time":1366000,"text":"We do not believe in violence."},{"time":1369000,"text":"No violence, no bombs, no guns."},{"time":1372000,"text":"That's not the way to solve problems."},{"time":1374000,"text":"Violence leads to violence, at least in my view."},{"time":1378000,"text":"So how do we solve?"},{"time":1380000,"text":"The tools for solving the problems are knowledge and understanding."},{"time":1385000,"text":"Know the facts, but see how they fit in the big picture."},{"time":1388000,"text":"Hard work and persistence --don't give up --"},{"time":1391000,"text":"and love and compassion leading to respect for all life."},{"time":1396000,"text":"How many more minutes? Two, one?"},{"time":1398000,"text":"Chris Anderson: One -- one to two."},{"time":1400000,"text":"Jane Goodall: Two, two, I'm going to take two."},{"time":1402000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1403000,"text":"Are you going to come and drag me off?"},{"time":1405000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1407000,"text":"Anyway -- so basically, Roots and Shoots"},{"time":1411000,"text":"is beginning to change young people's lives."},{"time":1414000,"text":"It's what I'm devoting most of my energy to."},{"time":1418000,"text":"And I believe that a group like this can have a very major impact,"},{"time":1425000,"text":"not just because you can share technology with us,"},{"time":1428000,"text":"but because so many of you have children."},{"time":1431000,"text":"And if you take this program out, and give it to your children,"},{"time":1436000,"text":"they have such a good opportunity to go out and do good,"},{"time":1440000,"text":"because they've got parents like you."},{"time":1442000,"text":"And it's been so clear how much you all care"},{"time":1446000,"text":"about trying to make this world a better place."},{"time":1448000,"text":"It's very encouraging."},{"time":1450000,"text":"But the kids do ask me --"},{"time":1452000,"text":"and this won't take more than two minutes, I promise --"},{"time":1454000,"text":"the kids say, \"Dr. Jane, do you really have hope for the future?"},{"time":1459000,"text":"You travel, you see all these horrible things happening.\""},{"time":1463000,"text":"Firstly, the human brain -- I don't need to say anything about that."},{"time":1467000,"text":"Now that we know what the problems are around the world,"},{"time":1470000,"text":"human brains like yours are rising to solve those problems."},{"time":1474000,"text":"And we've talked a lot about that."},{"time":1476000,"text":"Secondly, the resilience of nature."},{"time":1479000,"text":"We can destroy a river,"},{"time":1481000,"text":"and we can bring it back to life."},{"time":1483000,"text":"We can see a whole area desolated,"},{"time":1488000,"text":"and it can be brought back to bloom again, with time or a little help."},{"time":1493000,"text":"And thirdly, the last speaker talked about -- or the speaker before last,"},{"time":1499000,"text":"talked about the indomitable human spirit."},{"time":1502000,"text":"We are surrounded by the most amazing people"},{"time":1506000,"text":"who do things that seem to be absolutely impossible."},{"time":1510000,"text":"Nelson Mandela -- I take a little piece of limestone"},{"time":1513000,"text":"from Robben Island Prison, where he labored for 27 years,"},{"time":1516000,"text":"and came out with so little bitterness, he could lead his people"},{"time":1521000,"text":"from the horror of apartheid without a bloodbath."},{"time":1524000,"text":"Even after the 11th of September -- and I was in New York"},{"time":1528000,"text":"and I felt the fear -- nevertheless, there was so much human courage,"},{"time":1534000,"text":"so much love and so much compassion."},{"time":1537000,"text":"And then as I went around the country after that and felt the fear --"},{"time":1541000,"text":"the fear that was leading to people feeling"},{"time":1543000,"text":"they couldn't worry about the environment any more,"},{"time":1545000,"text":"in case they seemed not to be patriotic --"},{"time":1548000,"text":"and I was trying to encourage them,"},{"time":1550000,"text":"somebody came up with a little quotation from Mahatma Gandhi,"},{"time":1553000,"text":"\"If you look back through human history,"},{"time":1556000,"text":"you see that every evil regime has been overcome by good.\""},{"time":1560000,"text":"And just after that a woman brought me this little bell,"},{"time":1564000,"text":"and I want to end on this note."},{"time":1566000,"text":"She said, \"If you're talking about hope and peace, ring this."},{"time":1571000,"text":"This bell is made from metal from a defused landmine,"},{"time":1577000,"text":"from the killing fields of Pol Pot --"},{"time":1580000,"text":"one of the most evil regimes in human history --"},{"time":1583000,"text":"where people are now beginning to put their lives back together"},{"time":1587000,"text":"after the regime has crumbled."},{"time":1590000,"text":"So, yes, there is hope, and where is the hope?"},{"time":1594000,"text":"Is it out there with the politicians?"},{"time":1598000,"text":"It's in our hands."},{"time":1600000,"text":"It's in your hands and my hands"},{"time":1602000,"text":"and those of our children."},{"time":1604000,"text":"It's really up to us."},{"time":1606000,"text":"We're the ones who can make a difference."},{"time":1608000,"text":"If we lead lives where we consciously leave"},{"time":1610000,"text":"the lightest possible ecological footprints,"},{"time":1614000,"text":"if we buy the things that are ethical for us to buy"},{"time":1617000,"text":"and don't buy the things that are not,"},{"time":1620000,"text":"we can change the world overnight."},{"time":1623000,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}